sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor PlatformEngineer as Platform Engineer
    participant APIServer as Kube API Server
    participant Webhook as Validating Webhook
    participant Operator as Operator Pod
    participant LiveCluster as Cluster Runtime
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus Server

    PlatformEngineer->>APIServer: kubectl apply -f db-spec.yaml
    APIServer->>Webhook: Validate Custom Resource spec (valid replicas, storage, schema)
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Admission Allowed
    APIServer->>APIServer: Persist PostgresCluster object in etcd
    APIServer-->>PlatformEngineer: postgrescluster.database.production.k8s/prod-db created

    Note over APIServer,Operator: Informer detects new object via HTTP Watch connection
    APIServer->>Operator: Watch Event: ADD postgresclusters/prod-db
    Operator->>Operator: Enqueue key 'default/prod-db' in Workqueue
    Operator->>Operator: Worker thread pops key, starts Reconcile()
    
    Operator->>LiveCluster: Read current pods with selector app=prod-db
    LiveCluster-->>Operator: Found: 0 Pods
    
    Note over Operator,LiveCluster: Reconcile Action: Actual (0) != Desired (3) Replicas
    Operator->>LiveCluster: Create Primary StatefulSet pod (prod-db-0) and PVC
    LiveCluster-->>Operator: Pod & PVC Created
    
    Operator->>LiveCluster: Create Read/Write Service & Read-Only Service
    LiveCluster-->>Operator: Services Created

    Operator->>APIServer: Update Status subresource: Phase=Initializing, Replicas=1
    
    Note over Operator,LiveCluster: Wait for Primary to become Ready
    Operator->>LiveCluster: Create streaming replica pods (prod-db-1, prod-db-2)
    LiveCluster-->>Operator: Replicas Created

    Note over Operator,APIServer: Reconciliation completes with no error
    Operator->>APIServer: Update Status: Phase=Ready, Replicas=3
    Operator->>Prometheus: Export metric: postgres_operator_reconcile_success_total{name="prod-db"}
